snippet: Andre Iguodala made a career-high seven 3-pointers and scored 32 points for the Golden State Warriors, who handed the Philadelphia 76ers their first loss on Monday night.
abstract: Golden State Warriors beat Philadelphia 76ers, 110-90; other basketball scores noted.
lead_paragraph: Andre Iguodala made a career-high seven 3-pointers and scored 32 points for the Golden State Warriors, who handed the Philadelphia 76ers their first loss on Monday night.

headline.main: Iguodala Paces Warriors to Give 76ers Their First Loss
